========================================================================
                              Editorial
========================================================================
    I have been corresponding with an ex Fidonet sysop from Hong
Kong regarding the doings there, and what "we" should be doing
about them.  Truth is, what CAN we do about them?  Nothing
really.  Ultimately, only the sysops in a particular area can
remedy problems in that area.

    People talk about the "fidogods" as if they have some sort of
power to change things.  I know that personally, about all I can
do is print the articles that come in.  I cannot (and do not
want to) control anything outside my own BBS. It astonishes me
to be included in some mythical group of fidogods.  I have not
even met anyone else that seems to be included in that group,
let alone planned anything with them.  I probably have
FidoNews 12-19                 Page:  2                    08 May 1995

had posts from some, but the posts looked exactly the same as
the ones that came from points.  No more no less.

    Here in our own net, I am in the midst of a debate on
whether non-hubs should be allowed to vote in net decisions. As
I gave up being a hub a year or so back, I have been eliminated
suddenly from voting status to a non-entity.  I argue against it
the same as any other sysop in any other net.

    It is time that we started to develope new methods.  The
political shortcomings of fidonet are largely the result of
technological shortcomings.  We are stagnating, and we should be
doing something about it.

